## 🌿 Feature 2: Inaccessible Grassland Background Spawner
We replaced the boring, flat gray/black empty space outside the tilemap with a gorgeous, seamless grassland void.

* **Dynamic Grass Spawner**: Wrote and integrated [background_grass_spawner.gd](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scripts/background_grass_spawner.gd) into the game tree. At launch, the script scans the active tileset `Beginning Fields`, dynamically identifies the **most common grass tile** (detected as `source_id=43`, coordinate `(2, 1)`), and fills a massive `300 x 300` grid centered behind the map at `z_index = -10`.
* **Inviolable Boundary Collisions**: Preserved physical integrity! The spawner places background tiles *behind* the map, while [world_boundary.gd](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scripts/world_boundary.gd) builds invisible collider walls precisely around the boundaries of the playable map. The player and NPCs are physically prevented from leaving the map, but the screen now displays a beautiful endless grassland instead of a black void!

