## 👥 Feature 3: Refactored Dedicated NPC Character Scenes
We broke down the shared, generic entity into four fully custom, separate scenes to fulfill your teammate's design requirements.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class CharacterBody2D {
        +String agent_id
        +SpriteFrames sprite_frames
    }
    CharacterBody2D <|-- CommanderNPC
    CharacterBody2D <|-- CitizenNPC
    CharacterBody2D <|-- PriestNPC
    CharacterBody2D <|-- BishopNPC
```

* **Dedicated Scenes**: Built custom blueprints inside `res://scenes/npc/`:
  * [commander_npc.tscn](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scenes/npc/commander_npc.tscn) $\rightarrow$ Default `agent_id = "commander"`
  * [citizen_npc.tscn](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scenes/npc/citizen_npc.tscn) $\rightarrow$ Default `agent_id = "citizen"`
  * [priest_npc.tscn](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scenes/npc/priest_npc.tscn) $\rightarrow$ Default `agent_id = "priest"`
  * [bishop_npc.tscn](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scenes/npc/bishop_npc.tscn) $\rightarrow$ Default `agent_id = "bishop"`
* **Independent Resources**: Each scene carries its own **standalone `SpriteFrames` resource**. Your teammate can swap spritesheets and animations independently for each character!
* **Natural Coloring**: Cleaned up [npc_agent.gd](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scripts/npc_agent.gd) to strip the artificial modulated color tinting. All characters now render with their real, natural spritesheet colors!
* **Scene Swaps**: Replaced all generic references inside [game.tscn](file:///d:/court-of-whispers-godot/scenes/game.tscn) with our new individual character scenes.

